%h1 Meetup & conference video equipment

%p
  A little while ago we started getting over subscribed for the JavaScript group
  %a{ href: "http://www.meetup.com/BristolJS/", target: "_blank" }Bristol JS
  that I run. I wanted to give everybody who wanted the chance to watch the talks but we simply didn't have the capacity.

%p
  Filming the talks is a great way to give these people a chance to do so whilst opening our content out to the wider community.

%p
  We had some quite shoddy equipment to begin with which involved me filming the talks on my iPhone but when we started taking on sponsors this year we decided to give this equipment  an overhaul.

%p
  I was surprised to not find any information on what equipment was recommended. The closest thing I could find was
  %a{ href: "http://blog.confreaks.net/2010/10/my-recording-equipment/", target: "_blank" }this blog post
  from back in 2010. I decided that once I got all our gear sorted I'd write about it.

%p
  So here it is, a comprehensive guide of the equipment we use and why we use it. If you have any questions you can email me on
  %a{ href: "mailto:adam@lab.io?Subject=Message from lab.io", target: "_blank" } adam@lab.io

